title: Back from the road; Tribe gets ready for New Hampshire
text:
Back from the road; Tribe gets ready for New Hampshire William & Mary is back at home this Saturday when they host New Hampshire at 12pm. Post to Facebook Back from the road; Tribe gets ready for New Hampshire William & Mary is back at home this Saturday when they host New Hampshire at 12pm.  //on.wvec.com/1RJg4ja   Back from the road; Tribe gets ready for New Hampshire Brian K Smith , 13News Now 11:58 p.m. EDT October 14, 2015 CONNECT   
William & Mary's football team has taken the term "Road Warriors" to another level. Four of the Tribe's first five games have been away from Zable Stadium, but that changes this weekend. On Saturday at high noon, they take on 19th ranked New Hampshire. It'll be the second straight week they've taken on a ranked opponent. Tribe gets set for their home game against New Hampshire. 13News Now 
The Tribe is looking to get even with the Wildcats. They got beaten last year at their place 32-3. Players feel being out of town for the early part of their schedule will serve them well the rest of this season.  //on.wvec.com/1RJg4ja TOP VIDEOS
